Body:
Description: Hello,

We've recently moved our scanning from an Azure server to 2 new onprem servers and now the scan is failing. The error message suggests that the table is not created. Please assist.  Thank you!

What We've Learned Updated: client is OOO today, Friday 11/15/24
they said they will provide a response on Monday
Next Steps Updated: awaiting response and logs from client

**Active DirectoryGROUP_Active DirectoryGROUP_2.UsersJOB_AD_WeakPasswords_Custom

MSG_TYPETableNameMESSAGETaskNameERROR

Invalid column name 'extensionAttribute9'.

Â 

Invalid column name 'extensionAttribute9'.ADI Extended AttributesERROR

Invalid object name 'SA_AD_WeakPasswords_Custom_Result'.Weak Passwords Extended AttributeERROR

Unexpected exception: Encountered error: "No columns available for the table:'SA_AD_WeakPasswords_Custom_Result1' to display data." while generating report

ERROR

Report generation task failed.
Steps to Reproduce Updated: Post migration/ fresh install the needed attribute was no longer being collected via ADI

What We've Learned Updated: Found that the 'extensionAttribute9' attribute was not being collected by Jobs >> .Active Directory Inventory>> 1-AD_Scan  (ADI) job.

This is a recurred column for the Custom JOB_AD_WeakPasswords_Custom job

Next Steps Updated: With the attribute collection corrected we kicked off this scan per a mock schedule as well as staged ones for JOB_AD_WeakPasswords & JOB_AD_WeakPasswords_Custom.

The later two jobs will need to be run post the 1-AD_Scan jobs completion.

Awaiting job completion details.
